result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin Gerald Newhouse was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austin Gerald Newhouse is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austin Gerald Newhouse was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:10 AM Defendant Austin Gerald Newhouse in court.  Attorney Ellen Denise Craker in court for Austin Gerald Newhouse.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case.  State indicates defendant will plead to Count 2, recommend 45 days imposed and stayed for 1 year probation, conditions of DOC programming, $10 fine plus costs, 2 days credit.
Court recounts charges and possible penalties.  Defendant pleads no contest.  Court informs defendant of rights given up by plea. Defendant understands. No objection of factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds defendant understand proceedings and plea made freely, voluntarily and knowingly. Court finds defendant understands rights and is waiving rights freely, voluntarily and knowingly. Factual basis exists. Court finds defendant guilty. Count 1 is dismissed.
Court orders 45 days jail, imposed and stay for 1 year, conditions are DOC programming, $10 fine plus costs including domestic abuse surcharge, 2 days jail, 2 days credit.
